<paragraph blockId="43.[192,1440,833,890]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,527,833,857]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[543,630,834,858]" captionStart="Figures 83–88" captionStartId="70.[192,288,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,192,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-53@70.[192,1440,192,1857]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figures 83–88. Species distribution maps. 83) Bembidion giachinoi. 84) B. granuliferum. 85) B. hokitikense. 86) B. karikari new species. 87) B. mangamuka new species. 88) B. maorinum levatum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181790/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
). North Island: ND–Herekino. Opurehu River (
<quantity box="[1207,1268,834,858]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="42" unit="km" value="6.0">6 km</quantity>
